    "description": "A smooth ergonomic handle built from Blender's native modifier stack instead of hand-computed triangles: a 16-segment cylinder primitive smoothed by a Subdivision Surface modifier (2 viewport / 3 render levels), softened with a Bevel, and carved by a Boolean difference whose target is a small sphere object forming a thumb-rest indent. Blender's own modifier evaluation computes the real smooth geometry when the exported script runs - the document only carries the modifier description. This is the canonical pattern for organic threed shapes: primitive + subsurf + bevel, plus boolean cuts."
